On Masquerades and balls, and all the masks around us.

"The dance beckoned to me. _I was at a loss;_ all I could do once again was to throw on a mask and sway to the harmonic rhythm of society. I have come to realize _identity_ is simply another _mask_ to be worn. And so I will give ‘identity’ some variance, and don *every* mask. I will dance--*what else is there to do at a masquerade?*"